===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally {{zh-l|*𠳋}}, an {{liushu|ic|nocap=1}} in the {{w|oracle bone script}}: two {{zh-l|*又|hand}} in a configuration of commanding + {{zh-l|*𠂤|army}} – “to send; to dispatch”.

The {{zh-l|*辵}} component was later added in some {{w|bronze inscriptions}}, which is retained in the modern glyph.

===Etymology===
Usually identified as cognate to {{cog|bo|སྐྱེལ|t=send}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Hill, 2019}}). They can be reconstructed to {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*sV-kjarl}}.

